myexcelonline's 333 excel shortcuts

/ Formatting Cell Shortcuts /

- Applying Currency format: CTRL + SHIFT + $

- Applying Date format: CTRL + SHIFT + #

- Applying General format: CTRL + SHIFT + ~

- Applying Number format: CTRL + SHIFT + !

- Applying or Removing Bold formatting: CTRL + B

- Applying or Removing Bold formatting: CTRL + I

- Applying or Removing Strikethrough formatting: CTRL + 5

- Applying or Removing Underline formatting: CTRL + U

- Applying Outline Border to cells: CTRL + SHIFT + &
- Remove outline border to selected cells: CTRL + SHIFT + _

- Applying Percentage format: CTRL + SHIFT + %

- Applying Scientific format: CTRL + SHIFT + ^

- Applying time format: CTRL + SHIFT + @

- Copy selected cells: CTRL + C
- Paste selected cells: CTRL + V
- Cut selected cells: CTRL + X

- Check Spelling: F7

- Edit Active cell: F2

- Enter Current Date: CTRL + ;
- Enter Current Time: CTRL + SHIFT + ;

- Copy formula from above cell: CTRL + '
- Fill down from cell above: CTRL + D
- Fill right from cell left: CTRL + R

- Format font in Format Cells dialog box: CTRL + SHIFT + F

- Display Quick Analysis options: CTRL + Q

- Insert a note: SHIFT + F2
- Insert threaded comment: CTRL + SHIFT + F2
- Open and Edit comment: SHIFT + F2
- Open and reply to threaded comment: CTRL + SHIFT + F2

- Open Insert dialog box to insert cells: CTRL + SHIFT + +
- Open Delete dialog box to delete cells: CTRL + -
- Open Format cells dialog box: CTRL + 1
- Open Paste Special dialog box: CTRL + ALT + V
- Open Insert Hyperlink dialog box: CTRL + K

- Insert a Table: CTRL + T
- Show or Hide objects: CTRL + 6
- Show or Hide outline symbols: CTRL + 8
- Toggle Formula On & Off: CTRL + `



/ Drag and Drop shortcuts /

- Drag & Copy: CTRL + drag
- Drag & Cut: drag
- Drag & Insert: SHIFT + drag
- Drag & Insert Copy: CTRL + SHIFT + drag

- Drag to duplicate the worksheet: CTRL + drag
- Drag selection to worksheet: ALT + drag



/ Working with Formulas Shortcuts /

- Autosum selection of cells: ALT + =
- Calculate active worksheet: SHIFT + F9
- Cancel entry in formula bar: ESC
- Complete entry in formula bar: ENTER
- Copy value from above cell: CTRL + SHIFT + "
- Create chart in a new sheet: F11
- Create embedded chart: ALT + F1
- Define names for reference: CTRL + F3
- Display function arguments dialog box: CTRL + A
- Display message for error checking button: ALT + SHIFT + F10
- Expand or Collapse formula bar: CTRL + SHIFT + U
- Force calculate all worksheets: CTRL + ALT + F9
- Input array formula: CTRL + SHIFT + Enter
- Insert a Function: SHIFT + F3
- Insert Function Arguments: CTRL + SHIFT + A
- Invoke Flash Fill: CTRL + E
- Move to end of text when in the formula bar: CTRL + END
- Select text in formula bar to end: CTRL + SHIFT + END
- Open Macro dialog box: ALT + F8
- Open Visual Basic for Applications (VBA) editor: ALT + F11



